# UI Input Controls: Color and Date

- For any color input, use a color selector control (for example `<input type="color">`).
- Do not use plain text inputs for entering color values.
- If a custom UI is needed, it must still expose a visual color picker and preserve accessible labels.

- For date inputs, use the Flatpickr library as the date picker UI.
- Do not rely on free-text date fields for user-entered dates.
- Configure Flatpickr with consistent format, locale, and min/max constraints based on the feature requirements.

## Examples

```html
<!-- Good: color selector -->
<input type="color" name="accent_color" aria-label="Accent color" />

<!-- Bad: text input for color -->
<input type="text" name="accent_color" />
```

```javascript
// Good: Flatpickr date input
flatpickr('#publish_date', {
  dateFormat: 'Y-m-d',
});
```
